<HEADLINE> HK Provisional Legislature Meets To Discuss Bills </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 9 (Xinhua)--The Provisional Legislative Council
(PLC) of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) today
held a meeting to pass an immigration bill and debate a number of
other bills.
</P>
<P>
This is the first meeting of the PLC held in the Legislative
Council Building in Central, Hong Kong Island.
</P>
<P>
In today's sitting the PLC passed all three readings of the
Immigration (Amendment) (No 5) Bill 1997, which is about the
orderly immigration of children born, in inland areas of China, to
Hong Kong permanent residents.
</P>
<P>
Four other bills were tabled to the PLC for the first and
second readings, including the Legislative Provisions (Suspension
of Operation) Bill 1997, Hong Kong SAR Passport Bill, Chinese
Nationality (Miscellaneous Provisions) Bill and United Nations
Sanctions Bill.
</P>
<P>
Before the opening of the meeting this afternoon, a ceremony
was held for PLC members to sign the Affirmation of Allegiance
book. The PLC members were sworn in on July 1, 1997, at the
inauguration ceremony of the HKSAR Government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
