<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asia, Europe Urged to Enhance Better Working Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Asia and Europe will benefit
tremendously if they could enhance a better coordination and
synergy in their working relationship, said a leading organizer of
the Asia-Europe Business Conference being held here.
</P>
<P>
The remarks was made in the chairman's statement today issued
at the first Asia-Europe Business Conference.
</P>
<P>
Aburizal Bakrie, chairman of the conference and chairman of the
Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry, said the conference
which began on Tuesday has achieved a "significant step forward to
our future direction".
</P>
<P>
He said as the 20th century is closing to an end, Europe with
its economic wealth, science and technological knowledge will
continue to function strategically in the 21st century. But Asia,
with its continued dynamism and enthusiasm, will also have an
important role.
</P>
<P>
"We understand that the 21st century is a new challenging era
in the world business development. Whether we call it
globalization, regionalization, the borderless world, the new
world order or a universal economy, we know for sure that we have
to prepare much better than what we have done in the past," he
noted.
</P>
<P>
More than 500 participants from 25 Asian and European countries
have exchanged views on development of small and medium size
enterprises, the importance of improving trade and investment
facilitation and infrastructure and looking ahead on the future
direction of Asia-Europe business relationship, the statement
said.
</P>
<P>
The conference is a follow-up activity of the decision of the
First Informal Asian-European Leaders Meeting (ASEM I ) in
Bangkok, Thailand, in March 1996.
</P>
<P>
Some businessmen at the conference, which will end tomorrow,
will hold one to one meeting at the last day of the meeting,
Bakrie said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
