<HEADLINE> Minali Wins Fourth Stage in Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Nicola Minali of Italy won the
223-kilometer fourth stage of the Tour de France cycling race from
Plumelec to Le Puy-du-Fou on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Italian Mario Cipollini retained the race leader's yellow
jersey. But he admited he does not really expect to finish the
Tour de France, rode a shrewd race on Wednesday's competition.
</P>
<P>
Cipollini stole away to win an intermediate bonus sprint and
then never let Erik Zabel out of his sight to finish in fourth
place, just behind the German, for an overall lead of four
seconds.
</P>
<P>
Early in the day a woman spectator stepped out onto the road to
take a photograph and brought down Fabiano Fontanelli of Italy and
Spain's Vicente Garcia Acosta.
</P>
<P>
All three were taken to hospital for treatment and a hospital
spokesman said the woman had come out of a coma. 
</P>
</TEXT>
