<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UN Envoy to Visit Afghanistan Tomorrow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The UN Secretary General's
representative on Afghanistan, Nobert Holl, will leave here
tomorrow for Afghanistan to meet leaders of the anti-Taliban
alliance, the official Associated Press of Pakistan (APP) reported
today.
</P>
<P>
Holl's visit to Mazar-e-Sharif, a major city in northern
Afghanistan, will be part of continued diplomatic efforts to bring
the Afghan warring groups to the negotiating table, according to
the APP.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Afghanistan, Holl will discuss matters
relating to the set-up of a political commission with leaders of
the alliance.
</P>
<P>
The proposed commission will take care of the ceasefire,
exchange of prisoners and the outlines for a broad-based
government in Afghanistan, said the APP.
</P>
<P>
The first step to be taken indeed was a ceasefire because the
bloodshed had to end, Holl was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
"The main and final target is the setting up of a broad-based
government in Afghanistan," he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
