<DOCNO> XIE19970710.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Wants New Chapter with Pakistan: Gujral </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minister Inder Kumar Gujral
today said that India wanted to "start a new chapter" in its
relations with Pakistan, Press Trust of India reported.
</P>
<P>
"We want to start a new chapter with Pakistan," he told a
public meeting in India's Uttar Pradesh while speaking on India's
relations with its neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister said that India was also strengthening
relations with other countries in the South Asian Association for
Regional Cooperation (SAARC), including Bangladesh, Nepal, the
Maldives, Bhutan and Sri Lanka. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
