<DOCNO> XIE19970710.0017 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rampant Fee Collection Must Be Stopped: Vice-Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- All kinds of rampant fee
collection must be stopped to protect the legal interests of the
country's enterprises, Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo told a national
telephone conference today.
</P>
<P>
Wu, also a member of the Politburo of the Central Committee of
the Communist Party of China (CPC), noted that the CPC Central
Committee and the State Council have always attached great
importance to the issue of stamping out reckless levying of fees
or fines on enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Both the number of departments involved and the sums of money
collected are growing, Wu said, stressing that this has not only
increased the burdens on enterprises, eroded their profits, caused
the loss of state-owned assets and affected the enterprises'
performance, but also seriously undermined the relations between
the Party and the government and the people.
</P>
<P>
The problem must be solved immediately, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
The work will be headed by the State Economic and Trade
Commission and participated in by the State Planning Commission,
the Ministry of Finance, the Ministry of Supervision and the
Auditing Administration, according to Wu. 
</P>
</TEXT>
