<HEADLINE> Greece's Deficit Soars in Early 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Greece's current accounts deficit
rose by 32.5 percent in the first quarter of 1997 over a year
earlier, topping 1,627 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The figure stood against 1,203 billion dollars in the first
quarter of last year, the Bank of Greece said today.
</P>
<P>
In March, the current accounts, the broadest measure of a
country's economic health, registered a deficit of 753 million
dollars, down from 898.5 million dollars last March. 
</P>
