<HEADLINE> Survey Shows Record Trade Surplus Likely for Germany </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Germany's Chamber of Commerce and
Industry said today that a survey showed Germany was likely to
register a record trade surplus this year, which would top 100
billion marks and possibly exceed the 1989 record of 134.6 billion
marks.
</P>
<P>
It estimated that exports would increase by six to seven
percent, compared to 4.6 percent in 1996, and that imports would
rose four to five percent.
</P>
<P>
It based the outlook on a survey of various chambers of foreign
trade and trade commissioners in 75 countries. 
</P>
