<HEADLINE> Dalian Pulls Away in China Soccer League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion Dalian Wanda
kept its unbeaten run as it crushed Jinan Taishan 3-0 at the
eighth round of the China soccer league on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Dalian, which has scored seven wins and one draw, collected 22
points, nine clear of second-placed Shanghai Shenhua.
</P>
<P>
Chinese international Li Ming opened the scoring for Dalian as
he beat two defenders to find the net.
</P>
<P>
Power forward Wang Tao headed home a cross at the 78th minute,
putting Dalian 2-0 up. Wang Peng completed the tally with a
header at injury time.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai, 1995 champion, only managed a 1-1 draw against less
fancied Qingdao Hainiu. It was the fourth draw and the second
straight for Shanghai in the season.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Guo'an, which has a well-known slogan -- "Guo'an fights
for the first place", but has never finished better than the
runner-up position, downed Guangzhou Apollo 3-0 in Guangzhou.
</P>
<P>
All three goals were scored by foreign recruits.
</P>
<P>
In the day's other games, August First evened Guangdong
Hongyuan 1-1, Vanguards Huandao held Sichuan Quanxing to a 0-0
draw and Yanbian Aodong edged Tianjin Samsung 1-0. 
</P>
