<HEADLINE> Torrential Rain Hits Shanghai, Zhejiang Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Torrential rain hit this, China's
largest city today, leaving some 70 houses flooded and large areas
of suburban farmland inundated.
</P>
<P>
The rain started in the Shanghai area this morning, and the
highest rainfall reached 118 mm, according to the Shanghai
Anti-Flood Headquarters.
</P>
<P>
All officials and workers in charge of anti-flood work have
been mobilized to drain off the accumulated water in the city, a
headquarters spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, local people and troops stationed in neighboring
province of Zhejiang have also been mobilized in the fight against
severe floods that have washed away dykes, houses and sections of
railways in Xiaoshan, Zhuji and Quzhou cities.
</P>
<P>
Floods caused by heavy rain in the past four days inundated
stretches of the Zhejiang-Jiangxi railway line and stranded more
than 7,000 passengers on seven trains.
</P>
<P>
But the line resumed operation today, thanks to railway
workers' round-the-clock efforts to drain off the water.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
