<HEADLINE> China's First Jointly-Funded Foreign Trade Company Set Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Dong Ling Trading
Corporation, the first jointly-funded foreign trade company in
China, was set up here today.
</P>
<P>
It marks a breakthrough in China's foreign trade system reform,
analysts here said.
</P>
<P>
The company, approved by the State Council, is jointly funded
by the local Dongfang International Group, the Mitsubishi
Corporation of Japan and the Continental Grain Company of the
United States.
</P>
<P>
It has a registered capital of 12.5 million US dollars, 51
percent of which comes from Dongfang, 27 percent from Mitsubishi
and 22 percent from Continental Grain.
</P>
<P>
The new company has obtained a license from the Ministry of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation and will soon go into
operation.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, other enterprises in Shanghai are applying to set up
jointly-funded foreign trade companies, according to local
sources.  
</P>
</TEXT>
