<HEADLINE> Dalian Takes Lead in Using "Green" Bags </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Shops and markets in this port
city in northeast China today took the lead in the country in
using a new kind of material for shopping bags.
</P>
<P>
The new bags will replace the commonly used plastic bags, which
have been widely criticised for causing "white pollution."
</P>
<P>
The city government stipulates that shops in designated regions
should stop selling plastic bags.
</P>
<P>
Plastic bags now in stock are allowed to be used only until
August.
</P>
<P>
Dalian has nearly two million urban residents. A recent survey
showed that each of them used at least one plastic bag per day.
</P>
<P>
The new material, which can be absorbed by the nature, has
replaced old-style garbage bags in 300,000 families, according to
a local official. 
</P>
