<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Aspiration of ASEAN 10 Still on: Indonesian FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian Foreign Minister
Ali Alatas said here today the aspiration of an ASEAN 10 is still
on despite the decision by the ASEAN foreign ministers to postpone
Cambodia's entry into the regional grouping indefinitely.
</P>
<P>
The aspiration to have all 10 countries in Southeast Asia in
the grouping remained as it could bring more benefit to the
region, he said at the end of the one-day ASEAN foreign ministers'
special meeting here.
</P>
<P>
"We continue with the aspiration of ASEAN 10 but at this moment
we think that the wisest thing to do is to accept two countries
only in July," he was quoted by the Malaysian national news agency
Bernama as saying.
</P>
<P>
Alatas said that because of the aspiration, the ASEAN foreign
ministers meeting today hoped that rival parties in Cambodia could
resolve their differences in a peaceful manner as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN foreign minister decided on May 31 that Cambodia, Myanmar
and Laos will be invited to join the present seven-member grouping
on July 24.
</P>
<P>
On ASEAN's initiative to help Cambodia solve the crisis, Alatas
said ASEAN stood ready to contribute to a peaceful solution to
Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
Today's ASEAN foreign ministers' meeting agreed to send a
special delegation to seek an audience with Cambodian King Norodom
Sihanouk and to see the two rival prime ministers.
</P>
<P>
The delegation would comprise Ali Alatas, Philippine Foreign
Secretary Domingo Siazon and Thai Foreign Minister Prachuab
Chaiyasarn.
</P>
<P>
Malaysian Foreign Minister ASEAN Standing Committee Chairman
Abdullah Ahmad Badawi said, "We wish to continue seeking the
possibility of making contribution to the peaceful resolution to
the situation in Cambodia." 
</P>
</TEXT>
