<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Energy Consumption Up 3.6 Percent in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The total gross inland energy
consumption of the European Union (EU) reached 1,360.4 million
tons of oil equivalent in 1996, 3.6 percent up over that of the
previous year, it was learned here today.
</P>
<P>
Energy consumption per person averaged 3,650.6 kilograms of oil
equivalent, ranging from 1,778 in Portugal to 8,157.6 in
Luxembourg, according to Eurostat, the EU's statistical office.
</P>
<P>
The EU's energy dependency rate -- net imports as a proportion
of gross consumption -- remained at 48.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
With 12 of the 15 EU member states above this figure, the net
exporting rate of 11.6 percent of the United Kingdom and the low
dependency rates of the Netherlands and Denmark kept the average
down, Eurostat reports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
