<HEADLINE> Painting Exhibition Marking Hong Kong's Return Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 10 (Xinhua) -- A special painting exhibition
marking the historic occasion, Hong Kong's return to China, was
opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Opening the exhibition "Reunion and Vision -- Contemporary Hong
 Kong Art 1997," Chairman of the Provisional Urban Council Leung
Ding-bong said that the exhibition displays about 80 items of art
works, including Chinese painting and calligraphy, Western
painting, print-making, sculpture, ceramics, mixed media and
installation.
</P>
<P>
"It reveals local artists' responses and visions towards the
return of Hong Kong to her mother country," Leung pointed out,
adding that the exhibition assembled varied styles and themes and
some of the artists depicted the majestic landscape in China's
inland areas and scenic spots of Hong Kong in their paintings.
</P>
<P>
"Some praise Hong Kong's return by calligraphy while the others
 adopt different means of creation to express their passions
towards the city and admiration to the assiduousness of local
people, as well as voicing their hopes for a bright future," Leung
 said.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, jointly organized by the Hong Kong Museum of
Art and the Hong Kong Artists' Association, will be opened for the
 public in the museum till August 17.  
</P>
