<HEADLINE> Power Station Construction Contracts Signed in Qingdao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Two contracts for joint
construction of thermal power stations in east China's Shandong
Province were signed here today during the ongoing '97 Qingdao
Foreign Trade Fair.
</P>
<P>
Shandong's Zaozhuang City, the Finland-based Imatran Voima Oy
Company and Japan's Tomen Corporation will jointly invest to
launch a thermal power station company.
</P>
<P>
The company will be in charge of building a power plant with an
installed capacity of 24,000 kw in Zaozhuang City, which will cost
30 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Qingdao Huaneng Co. Ltd will raise 850 million
yuan (about one million US dollars) to set up a thermal power
plant at Pingdu City.
</P>
<P>
The power station, with an installed capacity of 100,000 kw,
will have an annual capacity of 518 million kwh, and will be able
to supply heat equivalent to 1.44 million tons of standard coal
each year.
</P>
<P>
The Canada-based Noble Investment Co. Ltd is to hold 30 percent
of the shares of the project, and an investment company from the
United Arab Emirates will provide a 20-year low-interest loan for
the project. 
</P>
