<DOCNO> XIE19970710.0058 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Regulation Bans Extravagance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Party and government departments
and officials who spend public funds pursuing extravagant life
styles will be severely punished, according to a regulation issued
by the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and
the State Council.
</P>
<P>
The regulation, dated May 25, 1997, says that the move is aimed
at fostering a hard-working and thrifty atmosphere, and further
curbing extravagant behavior.
</P>
<P>
The regulation stipulates that:
</P>
<P>
-- The construction and decoration of office buildings must be
put under strict control.
</P>
<P>
No office buildings of Party or government departments should
be decorated within three years starting from 1997.
</P>
<P>
-- The number of conferences must be reduced to the minimum.
</P>
<P>
The actual spending on conferences for the year 1997 should be
reduced by at least ten percent in comparison with last year, and
news coverage of meetings should be cut.
</P>
<P>
-- Celebratory activities must be restricted to those highly
necessary.
</P>
<P>
-- Spending public funds on extravagant meals or entertainment
is strictly forbidden.
</P>
<P>
-- The installment of telephones for individuals and the
purchase of mobile phones must be put under strict control.
</P>
<P>
-- Inspections must be restricted to those of practical
necessity.
</P>
<P>
-- The supply or change of automobiles must be strictly in line
with related stipulations.
</P>
<P>
-- A lid must be put on travel abroad at public expense.
</P>
<P>
The regulation notes that travelling abroad using public funds
in the name of inspection, study, training, business tendering or
attending exhibitions is forbidden.
</P>
<P>
The regulation urges the financial, monetary and auditing
departments to strengthen their management and supervision of the
matters concerned.
</P>
<P>
The Party and government departments referred to in the
regulation are CPC organizations, people's congresses,
administrative departments, organizations under the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference, courts,
procuratorates, labor unions, the Communist Youth League of China
and branches of the All-China Women's Federation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
