<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Construction of First Optic-Fiber Trunk on "Roof of the World" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Construction work on a 558-km
optic-fiber line in southwest China's Tibet Autonomous Region has
begun in Doilungdeqen County. The line is believed to be the first
of its kind in the region, known as the "roof of the world."
</P>
<P>
The line is a part of a 2,754-km optic-fiber trunk -- a state
key project for the 1996-2000 period -- and runs from northwest
Gansu and Qinghai provinces to the region.
</P>
<P>
The long optic-fibre trunk will link Lanzhou, the capital of
Gansu Province, and Xining, the capital of Qinghai Province, with
Lhasa, the capital of the region, and also the only provincial
capital city in the country without an optic-fiber line so far.
</P>
<P>
The line will be hooked up with the country's major optic-fiber
trunks, and is expected to give a hefty boost to the economic
development in the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970710.0061 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
