<HEADLINE> China's Speedy Development in Post and Telecoms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- China witnessed a sustained and
speedy development in the postal and telecommunications industry
during the first half of this year, dealing with nearly 81 billion
yuan in business turnover, a nearly 33 percent rise from the same
period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
During the six-month period, the country added nearly 5.7
million lines to its public telephone handling capacity, bringing
the total to more than 98 million lines.
</P>
<P>
It also added nearly 11 million telephone users during the six
months, lifting the total to nearly 73 million, more than 9.7
million of which are mobile phone subscribers.
</P>
<P>
There are an average of 70 telephones and seven mobile phones
for every 1,000 people in the country and an average of 240 for
every 1,000 in urban areas.
</P>
<P>
The number of pager users in the country has now surpassed 30
million, five million of which were added during the past six
months.
</P>
<P>
Postal savings had reached more than 231.8 billion yuan by the
end of June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
