<HEADLINE> Asian Culture Research Center Set up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Academy of Social
Sciences (CASS) opened a research institute here today to
intensify its studies on Asian culture.
</P>
<P>
Celebrating the occasion, CASS also kicked off a seminar with
the theme "Asian Culture Striding Toward the 21st century".
</P>
<P>
Addressing the seminar, CASS Vice-President Ru Xin said that
there is now a clear understanding among Asian people that all
countries in the region should uphold their own cultural heritages
while they advance toward modernization. They agreed that Asian
cultures should be honored and take their proper places in world
civilization.
</P>
<P>
"We have come to a historical moment that requires people in
Asia to take the responsibility to study and carry on their fine
cultures and traditions," Ru said.
</P>
<P>
He said the center will facilitate exchanges between Chinese
and foreign scholars and academic societies, and promote research
into Asian cultures.
</P>
<P>
Currently the center's research will concentrate on Indian
culture, Islamic culture and Confucianism. Comparative studies on
the east and west cultures is another priority, Ru said.
</P>
<P>
"We hope our studies will direct people's attention to the
active role Asian cultures play in modern life and provide
perspectives for solving existing social problems," Ru concluded.
</P>
</TEXT>
