<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Encourages Rapid Development of Chain Stores </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Li Lanqing has
encouraged the retail sector to open more chain stores nationwide
to provide convenience for urban residents.
</P>
<P>
"More chain stores and supermarkets should be opened in
newly-built residential communities which are far from urban
shopping areas. And there should be a rich assortment of
affordable commodities," Li told a national conference on chain
store business, which closed here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the fledging service sector will become the
mainstream in the future development of China's retail sector.
</P>
<P>
He said the State Council, China's highest governing body, will
continuously support the development of chain stores.
</P>
<P>
"Chain stores should lower prices through establishing and
improving the management of distribution centers, while reducing
intermediary costs," he noted.
</P>
<P>
"Mergers of small retail companies will be encouraged because
big chain store companies can provide standard services and be
highly competitive," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Internal Trade plans to develop chain stores to
speed up reforms in the commercial sector, he added.
</P>
<P>
More than 700 chain store companies have opened some 10,000
outlets across the country in the past two years. They are popular
with consumers because of their convenient services and affordable
goods. 
</P>
