<HEADLINE> China To Continue To Protect Chinese Citizens in Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman
Tang Guoqiang said here today that the Chinese Embassy in Cambodia
will, as it always has, provide all Chinese citizens in Cambodia
with consular protection and assistance.
</P>
<P>
While answering a question at a news conference, Tang said that
it is an important part of the work of Chinese embassies and
consulates in foreign countries to protect the just rights and
interests of Chinese citizens and legal persons there.
</P>
<P>
Reiterating that Taiwan is an inalienable part of China, Tang
said that Taiwan compatriots are absolutely under the consular
protection of the Chinese government.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Chinese Embassy in Cambodia has taken
effective and prompt measures to provide necessary assistance for
all Chinese citizens there, including Chinese citizens from Hong
Kong as well as Macao and Taiwan compatriots.
</P>
<P>
The situation in the Cambodian capital Phnom Penh remained
tense following days of clashes between the two ruling parties.
</P>
<P>
Heavy fighting broke out over the weekend between First Prime
Minister Norodom Ranariddh's FUNCINPEC party and Second Prime
Minister Hun Sen's People's Revolutionary Party.
</P>
<P>
At least 20 people were killed and more than 100 others wounded
in the three-day fighting which started Saturday. 
