<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Reception Marks 36th Anniversary of Sino-Korean Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese People's Association
for Friendship with Foreign Countries (CPAFFC) hosted a reception
this evening to mark the 36th anniversary of the signing of the
Sino-Korean Treaty of Friendship, Cooperation and Mutual
Assistance.
</P>
<P>
President of the CPAFFC Qi Huiyuan said that China and the
Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) have adhered to the
basic spirit of the treaty in the past 36 years, and that
bilateral exchanges and cooperation have been expanded over the
past decades.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Sino-Korean friendship, initiated and fostered by
the older generations of leaders of the two countries, has stood
the test of time and also been deeply rooted in the hearts of the
peoples of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Promoting Sino-Korean friendship is not only an unshakeable
policy of the Chinese government, but also a sincere hope of the
Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the conviction that the Korean people can overcome
difficulties along the path ahead, and make even greater
achievements in the cause of building socialism.
</P>
<P>
Song Pong Hwan, charge d'affaires ad interim of the DPRK
Embassy in Beijing, said that the treaty showed the common desire
of the two peoples to further develop DPRK-China friendship, which
is sealed in blood, and to safeguard peace in Asia and in the
world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
He added that with the care of the leaders of the two
countries, bilateral friendship and cooperation would continue to
grow.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Deputy Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan and other senior
