<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng today
expressed his thanks to Shoichi Hara, a noted Japanese rice expert
who has been teaching and spreading the technique of planting rice
with fewer seedlings in China for many years.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting with Hara here this afternoon, the premier said
Hara has made great efforts to popularize the highly productive
rice-planting technique in China, and has achieved notable
successes.
</P>
<P>
