<HEADLINE> Farewell Ceremony for Senior Catholic Bishop Held in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- A farewell ceremony for Bishop
Zong Huaide, late chairman of the Chinese Catholic Bishops
College, who died on June 27, was held at the Babaoshan
Revolutionary Cemetery in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
Bishop Zong was also chairman of the Chinese Patriotic Catholic
Association.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, Ismail Amat, Wang Zhaoguo, He Luli and other senior
officials also paid their last respects to the bishop, whose
remains was cremated after the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Zong was born into a Catholic bishop's family in Huantai County
in east China's Shandong Province in 1917. He was promoted to
priest in 1943. He served as acting Bishop of Shandong's Zhoucun
Parish in 1949 and the Bishop of Jinan Parish in 1958.
</P>
<P>
He was elected chairman of the Chinese Patriotic Catholic
Association, vice-chairman of Religious Affairs Committee of
Chinese Catholic Church and vice-chairman of the Chinese Catholic
Bishops College in 1980.
</P>
<P>
He was elected Chairman of the Chinese Catholic Bishops College
and the Chinese Patriotic Catholic Association in 1992.
</P>
<P>
Zong was a member of the fifth and sixth National Committee of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC),
and a standing committee member of the seventh and eighth National
Committee of the CPPCC.
</P>
<P>
About 500 people attended the ceremony, including officials
from the United Front Work Department of the CPC Central Committee
and the Religious Affairs Bureau of the State Council and the
Beijing municipal government, people in charge of the patriotic
Catholic organizations around the country, the representatives of
the Catholic followers in Beijing and Shandong, and
representatives from the national religious organizations.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
