<HEADLINE> 731 Filipinos Repatriated From Indonesia, Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 10 (Xinhua) -- A total of 731 illegal Philippine
workers and fishermen have been repatriated from Indonesia and
Malaysia since the beginning of this year, a military officer said
today.
</P>
<P>
Indanan Salih, information officer of the Philippine Armed
Forces, said in a statement that 498 of these repatriates came
from Malaysia and 233 came from Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
He said most of these repatriates were ferried home by
Philippine naval vessels and the latest arrival of 183 repatriates
came on board a commercial vessel from Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines has existing Border Crossing Agreements with
the Indonesia and Malaysia and by means of these agreements can
facilitate the return of undocumented Filipinos from any of the
two states.
</P>
<P>
A breakdown of the number of Filipinos repatriated from
Malaysia shows 107 returned last May 31, 208 returned last June 29
and the latest was 183 who returned last July 4.
</P>
<P>
From Indonesia, a total of 90 returned last April 13, 120 were
ferried home last April 28 while 23 came home last June 18.
</P>
</TEXT>
