<HEADLINE> UN Envoy Leaves for Mazar-e-Sharif </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The UN Special Envoy on
Afghanistan, Nobert Holl, left here today for the northern Afghan
town of Mazar-e-Sharif to try to bring the warring Afghan groups
to negotiating table.
</P>
<P>
Holl's visit to Mazar-e-Sharif is part of the continued
diplomatic efforts by the UN to achieve durable peace in the
war-torn central Asian country.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Afghanistan, Holl will discuss matters
relating to the set-up of a political commission with leaders of
the anti-Taliban alliance.
</P>
<P>
The UN Envoy will also call for the exchange of prisoners for
moving towards the objective of realizing a broad-based government
in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Before his departure, Holl said that he was going to seek an
agreement on cease-fire from the leaders as "it is the first step
because the bloodshed has to end." 
