<HEADLINE> Britain to Grant Emergency Aid to Montserrat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The British government announced
here today that it will give Montserrat 6.95 million pounds (about
12 million U.S. dollars) in an effort to help its people who are
severely affected by the volcanic eruption on the Caribbean island.
</P>
<P>
Britain's International Development Secretary Clare Short said
in a statement issued this morning: "We are taking emergency
action to deal with the crisis in all its aspects."
</P>
<P>
It was reported that some 20 people have been killed or
gone missing following the most serious volcano eruption on
June 25 of the Soufriere Hills volcano on the tiny island in
the eastern Caribbean.
</P>
<P>
Short said Britain would provide a further 6.5
million pounds (about 11 million dollars) to help build
emergency shelter for islanders.
</P>
<P>
"We are also drawing up an urgent package of options
which will be put to the people of Montserrat to enable them
to choose the best future for themselves in the face of this
disaster," she said. 
</P>
