<HEADLINE> Shanghai Securities Trading Shrinks Markedly in June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Both stock and bond trading
shrank markedly in this economic and financial center of China in
June, official figures indicate.
</P>
<P>
The stock market was in a correctional period last month, with
the benchmark Composite Stock Index down 2.72 percent from May to
close at 1,250.27 points.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that stock turnover in June dropped by
35 percent on a monthly basis to 135 billion yuan. Trading in B
shares, those reserved for overseas investors only, totaled nearly
two billion yuan, down 30 percent from May.
</P>
<P>
The trading volume of bonds plummeted nearly 50 percent from
May to 88 billion yuan, with bond repurchases down to 41.5 percent
those of May.
</P>
<P>
Last month fund prices also fell at the Shanghai market, with
transaction totalling 12 billion yuan, accounting for less than 27
percent of that of May.  
</P>
