<DOCNO> XIE19970710.0110 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Publishes Collection of World Constitutions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- More than 200 translators and
jurists have just published a collection of world constitutions,
expected to fill in gaps in the field of legal science.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by the research office under the Standing Committee
of the National People's Congress (NPC), China's top legislature,
the 2,200-page book with more than 4.68 million Chinese
characters, published by Qingdao Press, includes constitutions
currently in effect of most of the countries around the world.
</P>
<P>
The book also includes constitutional documents of many
countries in contemporary and modern times, and gives a brief
account of the constitution-making history of every country.
</P>
<P>
"It is necessary to depend upon, and give full play to, our
constitution in order to develop the socialist democracy and to
build a sound legal system," Wang Bingqian, vice-chairman of the
NPC Standing Committee today told a meeting on the publication of
the Collection of World Constitutions.
</P>
<P>
He noted that theoretical research should be made of the
constitutions, and the book provides precious first-hand material
for the research.
</P>
<P>
According to jurists, the book reflects the new changes in
constitutions, and in the political and economic systems of many
countries. It also uses new data in the field, which will benefit
a comparative study on constitutions, they said.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that China has made references to foreign
experience when formulating its constitution: In 1954, legislators
studied the constitutions of the former Soviet Union, Romania,
Poland and France when drafting the first constitution for new
China. And 28 years later when the constitution was revised, they
made a comparative study on constitutions of more than 30
countries.
</P>
<P>
China's new Constitution was promulgated and put into force in
1982. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970710.0111 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
