<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Investment Environment Improving </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The investment environment in
this largest economic and financial center of China has improved
significantly over the past years.
</P>
<P>
Official records show that investors from 73 countries and
regions have invested tens of billion of US dollars in Shanghai,
and over 200 international financial institutions and up to 1,000
multinationals have had a presence here.
</P>
<P>
Investors from the United States, Japan, the Republic of Korea,
the European Union, Singapore, Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan agree
that Shanghai enjoys apparent advantages in terms of the overall
investment environment, according to a recent survey.
</P>
<P>
They say that Shanghai's social and economic environment and
its rapid economic growth are most attractive to them.
</P>
<P>
Since 1992, the Shanghai economy has been growing at a rate of
more than 13 percent a year.
</P>
<P>
Improvement in the legal system and a profusion of talented
human resources also make Shanghai appealing to overseas
investors, experts say.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that currently more than 11,500 Shanghai
residents are working at overseas-funded enterprises.  
</P>
</TEXT>
