<HEADLINE> Air India to Begin Service to Singapore, Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Air India will soon start
services to Singapore and Kuala Lumpur with flights originating
from India's southern city Hyderabad on the "reciprocal landing
rights basis," the Hindustan Times reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Indian government has taken a decision on connecting
Hyderabad,  capital of Andhra Pradesh State, to both Singapore
and Kuala Lumpur following a request from the Andhra Pradesh state
government.
</P>
<P>
While the central government plans to commence these flights
from October-November this year, the Andhra Pradesh state
government is keen that the services start from August 15 to
commemorate the 50th anniversary of India's independence.
</P>
<P>
"The modalities are being worked out," official sources here
said. 
