<HEADLINE> Amnesty For Sri Lanka Army Deserters Declared </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 10 (Xinhua) -- An amnesty has been declared by
Sri Lankan Army Authorities for army deserters with effect from
today until midnight July 21, 1997, a military spokesman said
today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press briefing, the spokesman said Sri Lankan
Army Authorities made this decision consequent to a number of
requests by the parents of deserters and some deserters
themselves.
</P>
<P>
There are over 10,000 army deserters in the country, according
to the spokesman. The army authorities have granted amnesty three
times for army deserters since 1995.
</P>
<P>
The first amnesty was granted on June 1, 1995 and expired on
July  4, 1995. During that period 2,880 men returned. The second
was from November 24 to December 15, 1995. During the third phase
from June 10 to July 31 last year, 4,200 deserters had reported
back. 
</P>
</TEXT>
