<HEADLINE> Closure of Lusaka Brewery Plant Ordered for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Lusaka City Council (LCC) has
ordered the closure of the Makeni Brewery Plant in the capital for
polluting environment.
</P>
<P>
"The plant is emitting smoke within the residential area and
this is a nuisance," LCC Public Relations Manager Daniel M'soka
was quoted today by Times of Zambia as saying on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The plant has no sanitary accommodation, its employees have
not been certified fit to handle food and it operates without a
manufacturer's licence, according to the local newspaper.
</P>
<P>
The council has informed the Environmental Council of
Zambia (ECZ) about the illegal activities of the brewery plant
and the order was communicated to the director of the plant on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"We have served them with an enforcement notice and if they do
not close their premises within the 28 days limit, demolition
squad will move in," M'soka added.
</P>
<P>
The council has turned down the plea by the director of the
brewery to remove it from the residential area to light
industrial area.
</P>
<P>
The disclosure order was prompted by Environment Minister
William Harrington, who asked the LCC on Tuesday to probe into
the brewery plant after residents complained to him over the foul
smell from the plant. 
</P>
</TEXT>
