<HEADLINE> S.Africa to Help Rwanda Rebuild Country </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The South African government has
agreed in principle to help war-ravaged Rwanda to rebuild its country
and economy, said a source here today.
</P>
<P>
The assurance of assistance was extended by South African
Deputy President Thabo Mbeki to his Rwandan counterpart Paul
Kagame, who is currently in the country for an official visit,
following their talks on Wednesday in Pretoria, said the source.
</P>
<P>
The Rwandan government had asked for help in the military, the
police, health, education, trade and industry and the energy sectors,
according to Mbeki's spokesman Thami Ntenteni.
</P>
<P>
Ntenteni said, however, the details of the Rwandan request still
have to be worked out.
</P>
<P>
He also said an agreement had been reached that South African
delegations would be sent to Rwanda to determine the needs of the
Rwandans before working out the kind of assistance to be offered.
</P>
<P>
"South Africa recognises the fact that Rwanda needs this assistance
and is sympathetic to the positions of the Rwandans. We are going to
assist to the best of our ability," added Ntenteni.
</P>
<P>
Rwanda experienced a devastating civil war in 1994, which resulted
in the deaths of about one million people. enditem

