<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 19,200 Ugandans Flee to East Congo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 10 (Xinhua) -- At least 19,200 Ugandans have fled
their homes in the west to seek shelters in eastern Congo,
a report reaching here said today.
</P>
<P>
They left their home in Bundibugyo District to escape
harassment from the Allied Democratic Forces (ADF) rebels, Paul
Stramberg of the Office of the United Nations High Commissioner
for Refugees (UNHCR) told the New Vision.
</P>
<P>
Some 7,200 refugees are temporarily taking shelter in the eastern
areas of Beni, east Congo, said Stramberg.
</P>
<P>
More than 12,000 Ugandan refugees are believed in areas north of
Beni, and UNHCR is now trying to locate them, he added.
</P>
<P>
ADF, a rebel group operating in west Uganda, has invaded
Bundibugyo in mid-June to develop a food resource. Although
their intention was later foiled by the government troops, the
rebels had been threatening to kill civilians and caused an exodus
when they tried to escape government troops. 
</P>
</TEXT>
