<HEADLINE> China Supports Settling of Lockerbie Case </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman
Tang Guoqiang said here today that China supports all efforts for
seeking a settlement of the Lockerbie case.
</P>
<P>
Tang made the remark when asked about China's stand on the
recent new proposal by the Organization of African Union (OAU),
and the Arab League (AL), asking the UN Security Council to look
into settling the case.
</P>
<P>
Tang said that China appreciates the efforts made by the OAU,
the AL and non-aligned states, and supports the new proposal by
the AL and the OAU on resolving this issue, and all efforts and
proposals that could lead to a proper settlement of the case.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that the Chinese government has always
believed that disputes between states should be solved through
peaceful negotiations and consultations on an equal footing, and
that they should not resort to sanctions too readily.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that the parties concerned can develop a flexible
method and actively consider the new proposal for an early
settlement of the case," said Tang. 
</P>
