<HEADLINE> 26 Drugs Smugglers Killed in Iran in 10 Days </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-six drugs smugglers and
eight policemen were killed in clashes in the past 10 days in
Iran's northeastern Khorassan province, a press report said here
today.
</P>
<P>
The Persian-language daily Salam reported that a total of 17
tonnes of narcotics were seized and 900 smugglers were captured in
the province during the period.
</P>
<P>
General Bahram Nowrouzi of the Law Enforcement Forces in the
province was quoted as saying that 6,156 people who illegally
entered the Iranian territory were also detained and 141 assault
rifles confiscated at the same time.
</P>
<P>
Khorassan province borders Afghanistan where Iranian officials
claim some 6,000 tonnes of narcotics are produced annually.
</P>
<P>
Iran has been used as a transit route for smuggling opium and
heroin that are produced in Afghanistan and Pakistan, to Turkey
and eventually Europe.
</P>
<P>
Iranian authorities concerned said earlier that some 191 tonnes
of narcotics were confiscated from drug dealers over the previous
Iranian calendar year ending March 21, 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
