<HEADLINE> Chinese Mountain Resort Develops Tourism Route </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, July 10 (Xinhua) -- China's famous Lushan Mountain
Resort in Jiangxi Province has developed a better route for
domestic and foreign tourists.
</P>
<P>
The three-day route starts at White Deer Cave at the foot of
the mountain and ends at Donglin Temple. Tourists can not only
visit many natural scenic spots like mountain springs,
flower-covered valleys, and stone cliffs, but also can visit a
number of museums, botanical gardens, and villas.
</P>
<P>
Since the resort was selected in the list of World Relics of
the united Nations in last May, it has already received 148,900
domestic and overseas tourists.
</P>
<P>
Experts attending the 1997 Lushan Mountain International
Tourism Festival held recently in Jiangxi agreed that the route is
the best in the tourist resort's history. 
</P>
