<HEADLINE> China's First Auto-Leasing Chain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- China's first auto leasing chain
was established in Beijing today, another new development in the
chain-store business, following the opening of first chain store
for automobile sales in May.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Shijitong Auto Club was set up by the country's major
auto makers and will set up franchises in Shanghai, Tianjin,
Chongqing, Xi'an, Shenyang, Shenzhen, and 29 other major
cities. Anyone with a driver's license who is a member of an auto
club in any of these cities can rent a car at a rate below the
market price, said Guo Jiyuan, president of the club.
</P>
<P>
Guo said that his long-term goal is to set up auto-leasing
clubs in all cities which have airports. There are 101 airports of
different sizes in China.
</P>
<P>
Zhao Fengwu, an official from the China Industrial and
Commercial Administration, expressed optimism about the prospect
of the auto-leasing club, saying that it marks the beginning of
China's catching up to western countries, where they "take auto
leasing companies for granted."
</P>
<P>
The official said that China had more than 700 other
chain-store businesses with over 10,000 outlets by the end of last
year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
