<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Garment Industry Boosts Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, July 10 (Xinhua) -- In addition to fetching good prices
on the domestic market, China's garment industry has resumed its
export surge, helping check a downward plunge in foreign sales.
</P>
<P>
During the first quarter this year the garment output of
enterprises at or above the county level saw a 9.29 percent rise
nationwide from the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
A survey of national key garment undertakings shows that the
businesses earning comparatively bigger profits are mostly
involved in the production of shirts, suits, children's
collections, and eiderdown outer wear. The profit margins of these
products are 13.5 percent, 13.4 percent, 9.3 percent and 3.6
percent.
</P>
<P>
The country handled nearly 5.9 billion US dollars-worth of
exports of clothing and accessories during the first quarter of
this year, up 41 percent over the same period of 1996. The exports
included an increasing volume of high value-added products.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, thanks to price rises on the domestic market, the
garment industry recorded approximately 86 billion yuan in
domestic retail sales during the first quarter of this year,
accounting for 13 percent of the total retail sales of domestic
consumer goods.  
</P>
</TEXT>
