<HEADLINE> East China Developing Export-oriented Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The economic powerhouse of Jiangsu
Province in east China is making an effort to develop its nine
agriculture development zones into a showcase of export-oriented
agriculture for the country.
</P>
<P>
Over the past two years, the province has spent 640 million
yuan on building infrastructure facilities in the 21.2-sq-km
zones, which are located mainly in farming resource-rich areas,
such as Changzhou, Nantong, Xuzhou, and Nanjing.
</P>
<P>
By the end of May this year, the agriculture development zones
had approved the establishment of 298 enterprises, including 75
overseas-backed enterprises with a total investment of 88 million
US dollars. These enterprises have produced 41 million US dollars
worth of exports, said Xu Jianmin, an official at the provincial
government.
</P>
<P>
The Jiangsu Haisheng Group in the Nantong Agriculture
Development Zone co-funded an aquatic products company with a bank
from the Netherlands. The company involved an investment of nearly
30 million US dollars, and is competing profitably in the world
market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
