<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Anhui Agricultural Sector Growing Fast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, July 10 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province
witnessed a rapid growth in the production of grain, rape, meat
and aquatic products in the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
The province's summer grain yield totaled nearly 9.2 billion
kg, up four percent over last year's figure. The yield of rape
reached 1.3 billion kg, an increase of about 10 percentage points
over last year, its second-biggest harvest ever.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that the overall output of meat in the first
half of the year could reach 1.25 million tons, of which pork is
estimated at 870,000 tons. The total yield of poultry and eggs may
reach 550,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The province's aquatic production has also seen a rapid
increase, and the output is expected to exceed 520,000 tons, up
34.4 percent over the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Officials attribute this success to the province's stable
agricultural policies and increased investment in the sector.
</P>
<P>
Anhui spent more than 82.5 million yuan (about 10.3 million US
dollars) on agriculture in the first five months of this year, up
47 percent over the same period of last year. Banks have also
extended more agricultural loans this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
