<HEADLINE> India Approves 62 Foreign Investment Proposals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 10 (Xinhua) -- The Indian government has
approved 62 proposals with foreign direct investment worth 10.81
billion rupees (about 309 million U.S. dollars), the local press
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The proposals were cleared on the recommendation of the Foreign
Investment Promotion Board, an institute set up for simplifying
and speeding up the approval of foreign direct investment in the
country.
</P>
<P>
According to official sources, the proposals have export
projections of 12.82 billion rupees (about 366 million dollars)
each year.
</P>
<P>
The proposed projects, which are spread all over the country,
cover various sectors, including financial services, electronics,
tourism, textiles, auto accessories, engineering and consultancy.
</P>
</TEXT>
