<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Henan Benefits from Meteorological Satellite </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, July 10 (Xinhua) -- An advanced meteorological
satellite communications system, which boasts six times the normal
transmission speed, has gone into use in central China's Henan
Province.
</P>
<P>
The system, which enables the meteorology department of Henan
Province to communicate instantaneously with its counterparts all
over the country, plays an important role in preventing floods and
other natural calamities.
</P>
<P>
Henan is the country's fourth province to take advantage of
such a satellite. The provincial meteorological observatory and 16
regional stations successfully adopted the system in June as the
flood season is approaching. 
</P>
</TEXT>
