<HEADLINE> Indonesia to Evacuate Its Citizens in Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia is ready to evacuate its
citizens in Cambodia if needed, Indonesian Defense and Security
Minister Edi Sudradjat said here today.
</P>
<P>
"We plan to evacuate our citizens in cambodia by a military
airplane," Sudradjat said at a seminar on regional autonomy.
</P>
<P>
He said his government would continue to prepare for the
evacuation despite positive reports from Phnom Penh that the
situation in the country was gradually returning to normal.
</P>
<P>
He quoted the Indonesian embassy in Cambodia as saying that the
Indonesians in Cambodia were all safe so far.
</P>
<P>
The situation in Cambodia has remained tense since the clashes
between the troops of First Prime Minister Norodom Ranaridh and
Second Prime Minister Hun Sen last week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
