<HEADLINE> Northwest China Speeding up Infrastructure Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Gansu province
will put 6.9 billion yuan into 33 major construction projects this
year.
</P>
<P>
These projects include the electrification of the
Shizuishan-Lanzhou Railway, water supplies for Jiayuguan city, and
the Gansu Children's Hospital.
</P>
<P>
A provincial government official says that Gansu is giving
priority to energy resources and infrastructure like electric
power, the chemical industry, and communication, to create a
better investment environment.
</P>
<P>
The provincial construction supervision department has improved
project management to ensure that funds are properly used and
construction work goes smoothly.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the improved circumstances, major construction
projects added 2 billion yuan in industrial output, with 672
million yuan in pre-tax profits in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
