<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Large Lung Tumor Removed from Female Patient </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Doctors at the Shanghai No.1
Pneumosurgery Hospital have successfully removed a four-kilogram
tumor from a lung cancer patient.
</P>
<P>
The patient was a 44-year-old female employee of Anqing
Petrochemical Factory in east China's Anhui Province. Having
complained of chest pains and shortness of breath, she went
to this hospital in China's largest city to get treatment.
</P>
<P>
She was diagnosed as having adenocarcinoma of the lungs, a form
of lung cancer, and doctors there decided that surgery was
necessary.
</P>
<P>
During the six-hour operation, surgeons first had to deal with
a part of tumor that was on the pericardium, and then remove the
big tumor bit by bit from the lung.
</P>
<P>
The patient is now doing well in post-operative recovery.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
