<HEADLINE> Dhaka to Speed up Reforms in Financial Sectors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi Finance Minister Shah
AMS Kibria has vowed to speed up the financial reform and
dramatically improve the trouble-hit banking sector in the current
fiscal year, local reports said today.
</P>
<P>
"We have made every effort in every sector in order to speed up
reforms, but actual progress is quite limited. A lot of things
have to be done," he said in his concluding remarks at a workshop
here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Finance and the Asian Development Bank (ADB)
jointly organized the final workshop on the bank's support for
institutional development of the ministry.
</P>
<P>
The minister said qualitative changes could be attainable in
government activities through continuous endeavor.
</P>
<P>
"We are conscious about all the shortcomings and very much
sincere to overcome those," he said criticizing the mentality of
hiding problems and guarding data. "Nothing should be kept
secret," he added.
</P>
<P>
Bangladesh's stock market in the 1996-97 fiscal year
experienced a heavy blow by the biggest-ever stock manipulation
scandal while the banking sector was being strapped by huge amount
of defaulted loans.
</P>
<P>
The minister hoped that the ongoing ADB-sponsored reform
program would bring positive result within a few months in the
market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
