<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Passenger Car Sales Drop in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Passenger car sales dropped 16.7
percent in the Philippines in June as total units sold decreased
to 6,566 from 7,884 posted in the same month of last year, a
local newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
The decline in passenger car sales last month is the biggest
year-on-year drop recorded for this year, the Manila Chronicle
said, citing a report from the Chamber of Automotive and
Manufacturers of the Philippines Inc.
</P>
<P>
Passenger car sales for the first half of the year also
recorded a 7.8-percent drop from the year-ago level, with a total
of 43,879 units sold during the period.
</P>
<P>
The chamber's report attributed the unfavorable growth in car
sales to the technical correction of the market as a result of
accelerated selling last year and the reduction in the volumes of
applications.
</P>
<P>
After the strong performance displayed last year, car sales
have been on a decline since the start of the year partially due
to the slow processing and selective approval by banks and
financing institutions in car loan applications.
</P>
<P>
For this year, the government estimated the total passenger car
sales at 102,000 units, or 15 percent higher than the 88,648 units
sold in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
