<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Tamil Rebels Vandalize North Korean Ship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Tamil rebels have
vandalized the radar and other equipment of the North Korean Break
Bulk Carrier "Moran Bong," which they had hijacked earlier,
according to local press reports today.
</P>
<P>
The vessel, hired by Sri Lanka to transport goods to the Jaffna
Peninsula, was on its way to Colombo from Point Pedro Tuesday when
heavily armed Sea Tigers hijacked it at Millaitivu.
</P>
<P>
According to reports, the rebels had also drawn out the fuel
from the vessel which is lying about a mile off the coast of
Millaitivu and they are believed to have booby-trapped the vessel
to prevent any naval action.
</P>
<P>
A few days earlier the rebels, who claim a section of the sea
in the area to be under its command, set fire to an Indonesian
passenger ship and abducted its crew. Two Indonesian crew members
were later released. 
</P>
</TEXT>
