<HEADLINE> Myanmar Seizes 4,000 Kilos of Narcotics in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar authorities seized a total
of 4,268.5 kilograms of narcotics in May, the official daily The
New Light of Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
The seizure, which included 81.87 kilograms of heroin and
4,159.7 kilograms of different kinds of opium, was made by the
Myanmar Army units, police force and customs.
</P>
<P>
The drugs also included liquid chemicals and tablets.
</P>
<P>
The Myanmar authorities took action against 442 people in 345
drug-related cases in the month, the report said.
</P>
<P>
In April, 3,594 kilograms of narcotic drugs were confiscated in
the country, according to an earlier official report.  
</P>
