<HEADLINE> Prime Minister of St. Vincent Ends Visit to Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- James Mitchel, the prime minister of
St. Vincent and the Grenadines ended his five-day visit to Cuba,
today.
</P>
<P>
Mitchel described Cuba as important in the integration of the
area, and an important part of the Caribbean, "since we understand
the need to close ranks with Latin America and Cuba."
</P>
<P>
During his tour, Cuba and St. Vincent and Grenadines signed
three agreements on intensifying economic, scientific and
technological cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Mitchel had talks with Cuban President Fidel Castro on
national, regional and international matters. He said his country
would cooperate with Cuba in tourism, health and the training of
professionals.
</P>
<P>
Mitchel's visit consolidates ties with Cuba and the other
Caribbean countries after visits made there by prime ministers of
Grenada and Jamaica in April and May, the Cuban press said.
