<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, July 10 (Xinhua) -- An illegal logger together with
three other mahouts has been arrested by the Myanmar authorities
for his involvement in the death of an elephant used in pulling
illegal logs in the country's Htigaint township.
</P>
<P>
The official paper The New Light of Myanmar reported today that
the logger, in collaboration with the mahouts, used two female
elephants owned by the state-run Myanmar Timber Enterprise in
pulling logs which they had illegally felled in the Kolon Forest
Reserve on May 11.
</P>
<P>
One of the two elephants died of exhaustion in their move, the
report added.  
