<HEADLINE> Coffee Price Hike to Affect Consumption </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The coffer price hike
could cause a drop in consumption, said Mario Conti, director
general of the multinational food company Nestle.
</P>
<P>
"Several sources have calculated that consumption volumes in
North America could drop 10 percent this year compared with 1996,"
Colombian newspaper "La Republica" quoted Conti as reporting
today.
</P>
<P>
The Nestle executive has arrived in Colombia to take part in
the celebration of the 70th anniversary of the National Federation
of Coffee Growers.
</P>
<P>
According to Conti, the rise in coffee prices is due to
market speculations.
</P>
<P>
The director predicts that consumption in Europe will drop
less than in the United States. 
</P>
