<HEADLINE> Bomb Blast Kills 16 in Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 9 (Xinhua) -- An experimental shrapnel bomb
exploded at an airfield in southern Romania this afternoon,
killing 16 people and seriously injuring two others.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred when the bomb was being placed on a
home-made IAR-93 fighter plane in a test in Craiova, 235
kilometers west of the capital.
</P>
<P>
The bomb blast sparked the detonation of other aviation
ammunition.
</P>
<P>
The plane was destroyed and 15 defense industry workers and
military engineers were killed on the spot. One of the three
seriously injured died on the way to hospital.
</P>
<P>
Soon after the disaster, the Defense Ministry dispatched a
commission to investigate the causes of the explosion. President
Emil Constantinescu, who is attending North Atlantic Treaty
Organization's Madrid summit, sent a message of condolence to the
bereaved. 
</P>
