<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Investment Flowing Into Southern Fujian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 10 (Xinhua) -- More and more Hong Kong investment
is flowing into Shishi, a city in east China's Fujian Province,
with the total investment in the first half of the year hitting 60
million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
As the hometown of many Hong Kong residents, Shishi has
maintained good economic and cultural relations with Hong
Kong. And Shishi's improved infrastructure facilities have also
become a major factor in attracting investment from Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
There are so far dozens of projects each with funding above two
million US dollars; most of the investment has shifted from
labor-intensive to technology-intensive projects.
</P>
<P>
By the end of the first half of this year, the city had
received a total investment of more than one billion US dollars
from Hong Kong, making up 80 percent of the total overseas
financing in the city.  
