<HEADLINE> Auto Noise Disappears in Downtown Xi'an </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Xi'an, an ancient city in northwest
China, has become a little quieter since early this month when local
authorities prohibited drivers from blaring their car horns in
downtown Xi'an.
</P>
<P>
The number of motor vehicles in Xi'an has soared in recent
years, causing severe traffic jams, which has prompted more and more
drivers to lay on the horn, local urban traffic authorities say.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from the local environmental protection department
show that the traffic noise pollution has far exceeded that of
coal, smoke, and dust.  
</P>
