<HEADLINE> Guangxi to Host Vietnam Trade Fair in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, July 10 (Xinhua) -- Pingxiang, a border city in
southwest China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, will hold its
Fifth Trade fair from October 8 to 11.
</P>
<P>
Concurrently, the city will hold its first Border Tourism
Festival, at which a batch of international tourism projects will
be negotiated.
</P>
<P>
Exhibits at the trade fair will cover chemicals, building
materials, pharmaceuticals, farm machinery, foodstuff processing,
hardware, textiles and health care products.
</P>
<P>
