<DOCNO> XIE19970710.0226 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IDB Approves Financing to Upgrade Mercosur Corridors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American Development
Bank (IDB) today announced the approval of a 123 million U.S.
dollar loan to Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
The loan will be used to help the country reduce transportation
costs and upgrade national highways and bridges that are
international corridors to the countries of Mercosur, the southern
South America Common Market.
</P>
<P>
The resources will help rehabilitate and improve 520 kms of
national highways and 26 bridges that are on integration corridors
and also upgrade the quality of pavement on 360 kms of roads in
the periphery of Montevideo.
</P>
<P>
The project is part of the broad framework of increasing
integration with the other countries of Mercosur, and roads and
bridges will be upgraded according to Mercosur standards.
</P>
<P>
The total cost of the project is some 176 million dollars. In
addition to the IDB loan, local counterpart funds total 53 million
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
