<HEADLINE> EC Grants $15m for Ethiopia's Food Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission (EC)
today signed an agreement promising to grant Ethiopia 99 million
Birr (about 14.6 million U.S. Dollars) to help it secure food
security.
</P>
<P>
A press release issued by the Ethiopian government said the
grant will be used to strengthen the various activities and
institution involved in improving food security in Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
The release said about 7.8 million U.S. Dollars of the grant
will be used to promote employment generating schemes in Tigray,
Amhara, Oromia and Southern People's Regions while about 2.7
million Dollars will be used in improving the agrometeorological
service aimed at enhancing agricultural production in the
country.
</P>
<P>
The remainers will be channeled for strengthening the early
warning system and assessment and monitoring of soil erosion
problems in Ethiopia as well as for the development and
implementation of relief transport and logistics plan in various
areas of the countryside, the release added. 
</P>
