<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nearly 300 Ethiopian Children Adopted Annually </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Close to 300 Ethiopian
children are taken by adoption annually, the Ethiopian News
Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Dinkalem Betru, head of the adoption service team of the
Children and Youth affairs Organization told local journalists
that a total of 3,000 children were given to foreign fosters
since 1982.
</P>
<P>
She disclosed that only 32 children were taken by local foster
parents over the past 15 years, and said there are almost no
Ethiopian parents who seek to take children by adoption.
</P>
<P>
''All the children taken by adoption are below the age of 14
and are either orphans, abandoned or with parents suffering from
incurable diseases,'' she said.
</P>
<P>
Betru said her organization monitors the situation in which
the children have been taken out of the country by foreign
adoptive parents, adding that ''at the age of 18, the children
enjoy the right to decide to remain in the countries of their
adoption or return to their native country.'' 
</P>
