military operations in southeastern region of Turkey and northern
Iraq to wipe out the PKK rebels.
</P>
<P>
According to figures issued by the General Staff, at least
2,500 PKK rebels have been killed since 50,000-strong Turkish
government troops launched a cross-border incursion in northern
Iraq on May 14.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a 13-year-old separatist war in
eastern and southeastern Turkey in an attempt to establish an
independent Kurdish state. 
