<HEADLINE> US Considering More Food Aid for DPRK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 9 (Xinhua) -- The United States is considering
to provide more food aid to the Democratic People's Republic of
Korea (DPRK) after the U.N. World Food Program launched a new
appeal, the State Department said today.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the World Food Program called for an additional 46
million dollars in food aid to boost its supplies for DPRK
children.
</P>
<P>
State Department spokesman Nicholas Burns told reporters that
a formal U.S. response to the appeal is expected shortly as
there is "some degree of urgency" to the food shortages there.
</P>
<P>
"We're going to give this very serious consideration," he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
