<HEADLINE> Israelis, Palestinians Discuss Mid-East Peace in Athens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 9 (Xinhua) -- Israelis and Palestinians met here
today to discuss the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
The non-binding three-day meeting, the result of a Greek
government initiative, is attended by deputies, academics and
prominent figures from Israel as well as several Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will be addressed by Greece's Foreign Minister
Theodoros Pangalos and Foreign Undersecretary Yiannos Kranidiotis.
</P>
<P>
The Greek Foreign Ministry said in an announcement today that
Athens was watching developments in the Middle East with
particular interest, developments which affect stability and
security in the Balkan region and beyond.
</P>
<P>
"This meeting is part of continuous efforts being made by our
country towards all sides to promote the peace process, which is
at a particularly delicate and crucial phase at present," the
announcement said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
